BOKSBURG - The search for a five-year-old boy trapped inside a disused mine in Boksburg is due to resume this morning. The search was halted late Monday afternoon.READ: Boy trapped in mine shaft for daysThe boy fell into a mineshaft at the Jerusalem informal settlement on Saturday while playing with friends.Rescue officials have been working around the clock in an effort to find him.Ground conditions have however made it too risky for search teams to enter the mine and cameras have been sent down instead.eNCA